"1328–1362","1267–1328":"1267–1328","1270–1309":"1270–1309","1304":"1304","1267":"1267","1222":"1222","1298":"1298","1165":"1165","1362":"1362","1309":"1309","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","Ingelmunster, West Flanders, Belgium":"Ingelmunster, West Flanders, Belgium","Ninove, Flandre-Orientale, Belgique":"Ninove, East Flanders, Belgium","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Rodes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Catalan (<b>Rodés</b>): habitational name from any of several places called Rodés, mainly those in El Pallars and El Conflent districts, in northern Catalonia.","Catalan: variant of   Roda  , from Catalan <i>rodes</i>, plural of <i>roda</i> ‘wheel’.","English: variant of   Rhodes  . Compare   Rhode  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rudes","meanings":["Americanized form of Croatian and Slovenian <b>Rudež</b>: nickname derived from <i>rud</i> ‘red, reddish’, or, alternatively, from <i>rud</i> ‘curly’ (standard Slovenian <i>rod</i>; compare   Rodes  ). In Croatia, the surname is also found in the form <b>Rudeš</b>."]},{"name":"Roda","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Arturo, Francisco, Domingos, Manuel, Mario, Alfredo, Amandio, Andres, Angel, Eduardo, Elia, Gustavo, Joaquim.","Catalan: habitational name from any of various places called Roda, for example Roda de Ter, Roda de Berà, Roda de Ribagorça, from Catalan <i>roda</i> ‘wheel’ (from Latin <i>rota</i>), possibly denoting a waterwheel.","German: habitational name from any of numerous places, particularly in central eastern Germany, named Roda or Rhoda."]},{"name":"Rodas","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Carlos, Luis, Jorge, Juan, Ana, Jaime, Rafael, Elvira, Manuel, Miguel, Raul.","Catalan: Castilianized form of   Rodes   2.","Galician and Portuguese: habitational name from any of the three places in Galicia, Spain, named Rodas (in Lugo, Ourense, and Pontevedra provinces), from the plural of <i>roda</i> ‘wheel’."]}]},{"name":"Gerad","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’ + <i>wald</i> ‘rule’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. There has been some confusion with   Gerard .  It died out in England at the end of the 13th century. However, it continued to be popular in Ireland, where it had been brought in the 12th century at the time of Strongbow's invasion. It was used in England in the 17th century and revived in the 19th century, along with several other long-extinct names of Norman, Old English, and Celtic origin, and is now more common than <i>Gerard</i>, which survived all along as an English ‘gentry’ name."],"variants":[{"name":"Jerrold","meanings":["Rare variant of   Gerald  , probably a transferred use of the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]},{"name":"Lii","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Much reduced form of   Elisabet  , first used in the early years of the 20th century and frequently found as the second element of compound names such as <i>Anne-Lis</i>, <i>Ing-Lis</i>, and <i>Maj-Lis</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gerad Lii de Rodes was born as the son of Gérard de Rode III and Isabelle van Nevele. He had at least 1 daughter with Clarisse van Eksaarde. He died in 1328."},"et":{"–1328":"–1328","1304–Female":"1304–Surnud","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1328–1362":"1328–1362","1267–1328":"1267–1328","1270–1309":"1270–1309","1304":"1304","1267":"1267","1222":"1222","1298":"1298","1165":"1165","1362":"1362","1309":"1309","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","Ingelmunster, West Flanders, Belgium":"Ingelmunster, West-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Ninove, Flandre-Orientale, Belgique":"Ninove, Oost-Vlaanderen, Belgia"},"fi":{"–1328":"–1328","1304–Female":"1304–Kuollut","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1328–1362":"1328–1362","1267–1328":"1267–1328","1270–1309":"1270–1309","1304":"1304","1267":"1267","1222":"1222","1298":"1298","1165":"1165","1362":"1362","1309":"1309","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","Ingelmunster, West Flanders, Belgium":"Ingelmunster, West-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Ninove, Flandre-Orientale, Belgique":"Ninove, Oost-Vlaanderen, Belgia"},"fr":{"–1328":"–1328","1304–Female":"1304–Décédée","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1328–1362":"1328–1362","1267–1328":"1267–1328","1270–1309":"1270–1309","1304":"1304","1267":"1267","1222":"1222","1298":"1298","1165":"1165","1362":"1362","1309":"1309","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","Ingelmunster, West Flanders, Belgium":"Ingelmunster, Flandre occidentale, Belgique","Ninove, Flandre-Orientale, Belgique":"Ninove, Flandre-Orientale, Belgique","lifeSummary":"Gerad Lii de Rodes est né, fils de Gérard de Rode III et Isabelle van Nevele. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Clarisse van Eksaarde. Il est décédé en 1328."},"de":{"–1328":"–1328","1304–Female":"1304–Verstorben","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1328–1362":"1328–1362","1267–1328":"1267–1328","1270–1309":"1270–1309","1304":"1304","1267":"1267","1222":"1222","1298":"1298","1165":"1165","1362":"1362","1309":"1309","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","Ingelmunster, West Flanders, Belgium":"Ingelmunster, W